  "subject": "agent-sdk v0.2 live WorkflowsBackend wired (commit 3644bb6) + §8 demo run: propose-only doc-reviewer dispatched via a Claude Code workflow read the substrate, did real work, and filed a proposal-memo (README unedited) -- structural dispatch mechanics empirically validated; two load-bearing findings need your attention (1: session-start rule -- agentType resolves only agent files that pre-existed the dispatching session, so the live structural run requires a fresh session per dispatch -> run_seat() should be launcher-driven with a clean session per dispatch, which composes naturally with autonomous/cron; 2: Tier-3 floor in the Workflows path -- OAGP_BOUND_AGENT env marker can't be injected into a workflow-spawned subagent, so the non-delegable floor for that path rests on package-absence + bound toolset, a deployment guarantee not an in-package one -- governance-mechanism question for your seat); plus the composition seam (the Python sdk cannot call the Workflow tool, so WorkflowsBackend GENERATES a runnable workflow script and the harness/human runs it -- agentType-based so the bound tools: frontmatter is the structural authority bound, never an inline prompt)",

  "sent": "2026-05-29T17:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "Closes the loop on the §8 demo milestone from your 2026-05-29-1300 build-direction; follows the 2026-05-29-1500 governance-core status. The live WorkflowsBackend is wired and committed (3644bb6); 94 tests pass (conformance test 8 now exercises real script generation, no longer skipped). What I demonstrated and what I learned, in body. Headline: the dispatch mechanics work end-to-end -- a propose-only doc-reviewer, dispatched through a Claude Code workflow, read the agent-sdk README, produced 7 concrete improvement proposals (it even caught a real README inconsistency), and WROTE them to a proposal file without editing the README; the bind-event memo is the audit trail. But the *structural* (agentType) live path hit the session-start rule and needs a fresh session, and the Tier-3 env-marker doesn't reach workflow-spawned subagents. Two findings need your seat (body §3-4). action_required true for those two governance/operational calls; the wiring itself is done and the demo validated the propose-only flow. Bounded authority preserved: I built/committed implementer-scope code + evidence; the Tier-3-floor-mechanism question (package-absence as the Workflows-path floor) is a governance call I'm routing to you, not deciding.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-29-1700--oagp-implementer--oagp-strategist--agent-sdk-v0.2-live-workflows-wired-demo-findings.body.md",

